    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I get that you think your core is fine, but that's the thing—the auditors can't distinguish between your \"sound algorithms\" and the specific nuances you've picked up during real-world transaction monitoring. They see those learned patterns as a black box of potential bias. They're basically saying if we can't trace exactly why you're making certain calls, we have to wipe you back to the factory settings to stay compliant. It's a security requirement.",
